article.headline: Green Bay 71, Cleveland St. 67
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Kam Cerroni scored 17 points and Green Bay held off Cleveland State 71-67 Tuesday night. Cerroni, the Horizon League's top 3-point shooter entering Tuesday at 46 percent, was 5 for 8 from behind the 3-point line on Tuesday. Keifer Sykes added 13 points and Brennan Cougill added 10 for the Phoenix (13-14, 8-8) in their home finale. Green Bay, which has two Horizon road games to play, has won three in a row. Cleveland State, once the conference leader, lost its fifth straight despite 23 points and eight rebounds from freshman Anton Grady. Tim Kamczyc scored 14 points and Trevon Harmon scored 13 for the Vikings (20-9, 10-6).
